<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-01-18T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-01-18T15:00:00-05:00" n="706" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d706">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">611.3531/119: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Argentina</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Bliss</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Buenos
                                        Aires</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-01-18T17:00:00-03:00">January 18, 1933—5
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received January 18—4:52 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>9. Your 6, January 17, 4 p.m. Minister for Foreign Affairs has only
                            replied with generalities in conversation. Today he expressed surprise
                            that I had not yet received his written reply to my notes and said it
                            would be delivered without delay.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Bliss</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>